\pard\plain \fi720\sl288\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 I think it\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s very important to remember that prose is not what makes scary things scary and horrifying, it\u8217\'92s what\u8217\'92s happening that makes it scary and horrifying.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Too often, the prose overindulges in simple ideas. For example:}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 >}{\f0\fs24\b0 Hunger.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 >Raw, endless, devouring. A starvation that hollowed him out to the core. A need to consume and fill a void that stretched far beyond him, pulling at his edges until he couldn't tell where he ended and it began.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 All that, just to communicate: insatiable hunger. If you want to dwell on that hunger, each clause needs to add nuance to that feeling. As of now, they\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92re all communicating the same thing: this hunger obliterates his identity.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 And then elsewhere, the prose obscures ideas, instead of enhancing them:}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 >\~Emptiness, claustrophobic in its totality}{ }
\par\plain 
\par\plain {This expression totally robs the underlying idea of it\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s force. That underlying idea being something like: \u8220\'93The emptiness overwhelms him\u8221\'94. And then the expression itself is too much of a stretch. }
\par\plain 
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Cliche (not many of these, but they\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92re there):}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 >}{\f0\fs24\b0 the void answered back}{ }
\par\plain 
\par\plain {>couldn't tell where he ended and it began.}
\par\plain 
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0}